SUMMARY:Deadline: The Blackstone Publishing Novel Initiative 2026 (with The
  Black List)
DESCRIPTION:A partnership between The Black List and Blackstone Publishing 
 to identify an unpublished manuscript for a $25\,000 publishing deal. The 
 Black List helps Blackstone shortlist outstanding manuscripts submitted on
  blcklst.com during the submission period. Open to manuscripts in all genr
 es\, with particular interest in work that elevates familiar themes (love\
 , adventure\, guilt\, desire\, betrayal\, family\, identity\, obsession) f
 rom fresh\, compelling perspectives\, especially thrillers\, high-concept 
 mysteries\, romances and horror. REQUIREMENTS: post an original manuscript
  on blcklst.com\, receive at least one evaluation while hosted there (once
  evaluated\, a manuscript can be submitted to any eligible partnership at 
 no additional cost)\, and opt in to the program during the submission peri
 od. Submitted manuscripts must not be under contract elsewhere\; no featur
 e\, pilot\, play or musical submissions are eligible. Applicants must be a
 t least 18 and the sole owner of all rights to wholly original material\, 
 and must agree to the Submission Agreement (which includes legally binding
  terms such as arbitration). If selected\, the writer may enter into a boo
 k deal negotiated in good faith. Writing teams are allowed\, but every mem
 ber must comply and all must opt out if any member becomes ineligible. Not
 e: submitting requires being logged in to blcklst.com with an uploaded pro
 ject (the site charges separately for hosting and evaluations). Deadline J
 une 9\, 2026.\n\nOrganisation: The Black List and Blackstone Publishing\nL
 ocation: Online (manuscripts hosted on blcklst.com)\nAward: A $25\,000 pub
 lishing deal with Blackstone Publishing for the selected manuscript.\nDura
 tion: Submission period November 20\, 2025 to June 9\, 2026\n\nMore: https
 ://blcklst.com/programs/blackstone-publishing-novel-initiative?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://blcklst.com/programs/blackstone-publishing-novel-initiative?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Online (manuscripts hosted on blcklst.com)
