SUMMARY:Deadline: Emerging Authors: Frankfurter Seilschaften
DESCRIPTION:Frankfurter Seilschaften is a Pro Helvetia mentoring initiative
  pairing emerging Swiss literary practitioners with established authors du
 ring the Frankfurt Book Fair. To be eligible as an emerging author\, appli
 cants must have completed their artistic training or presented their work 
 publicly for the first time within the last five years\; the call also inc
 ludes professional writers who identify as FINTA. ELIGIBILITY: requires a 
 connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent residency with
  regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to practitioners wit
 hout a Swiss connection. WHAT IS OFFERED: hotel and travel expenses\, per 
 diems\, and trade fair passes. Submission deadline 1 September (23:59 CEST
 ). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss
  Arts Council)\nLocation: Emerging authors with a connection to Switzerlan
 d\; also open to professional writers who identify as FINTA.\nAward: Hotel
  and travel expenses\, per diems\, and trade fair passes (amounts not spec
 ified). No application fee.\nDuration: Mentoring during the Frankfurt Book
  Fair\; deadline 1 September.\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-supp
 ort/emerging-authors-frankfurter-seilschaften?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/emerging-authors-frankfurter-sei
 lschaften?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Emerging authors with a connection to Switzerland\; also open to p
 rofessional writers who identify as FINTA.
END:VEVENT
