DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's literary creation grant supports the development
  of literary projects intended for publication\, including fiction\, child
 ren's and youth literature\, poetry\, drama\, and spoken word. Applicants 
 must have prior published work\, a premiere\, or professional performances
 . ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, o
 r permanent residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not
  open to practitioners without a Swiss connection. AMOUNT: up to CHF 25\,0
 00 for writing\, CHF 18\,000 for theatre texts\, or CHF 15\,000 for perfor
 mative literary projects. Deadlines twice a year: 1 March (23:59 CET) and 
 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisati
 on: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerland-based authors
  and collectives.\nAward: Up to CHF 25\,000 (writing)\, CHF 18\,000 (theat
 re texts)\, or CHF 15\,000 (performative literary projects). No applicatio
 n fee.\nDuration: Creation phase for a literary project intended for publi
 cation\; deadlines twice yearly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: https:
 //prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/literary-creation-grant?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
