SUMMARY:Deadline: Writing in Residency
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's Writing in Residency programme provides residenc
 y opportunities (for example Traduki in Southeast Europe or Art Omi) for a
 uthors and translators to develop or research projects. Applicants must ha
 ve prior professionally published work. ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection
  to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent residency with regular a
 rtistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to practitioners without a Swi
 ss connection. WHAT IS OFFERED: travel and accommodation costs (varying by
  destination)\, plus childcare support of up to CHF 1\,000 per month for a
 pplicants with caregiving responsibilities. Submission deadline 1 Septembe
 r (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro He
 lvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerland-based authors and trans
 lators\; residencies at partner locations abroad (e.g. Traduki in Southeas
 t Europe\, Art Omi).\nAward: Travel and accommodation costs (vary by desti
 nation)\; childcare support up to CHF 1\,000 per month for applicants with
  caregiving responsibilities. No application fee.\nDuration: Residency to 
 develop or research a project\; deadline 1 September.\n\nMore: https://pro
 helvetia.ch/en/find-support/writing-in-residency?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
