SUMMARY:Deadline: Cullman Center Fellowships 2027-28 (New York Public Libra
 ry)
DESCRIPTION:The Cullman Center for Scholars and Writers at the New York Pub
 lic Library awards fifteen fellowships a year to writers and scholars (fic
 tion\, nonfiction\, poetry\, playwriting\, translation\, and academic rese
 arch) whose projects draw on the Library's collections. Fellows receive US
 D 90\,000\, an office\, and full research access for a September-May term 
 in residence. Open internationally. Deadline 25 September 2026\, 5pm EDT\;
  apply via the NYPL online application portal.\n\nOrganisation: Dorothy an
 d Lewis B. Cullman Center for Scholars and Writers\, New York Public Libra
 ry\nLocation: New York City\, United States. Open internationally\; fellow
 s work in residence at NYPL's Stephen A. Schwarzman Building.\nAward: USD 
 90\,000 stipend\, plus an office at the library\, full access to collectio
 ns\, and a September-May term. No application fee.\nDuration: September 20
 27 to May 2028\, in residence at the New York Public Library.\n\nMore: htt
 ps://www.nypl.org/about/fellowships-institutes/cullman-center-scholars-wri
 ters/fellowships?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
