DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Alfred P. Sloan Foundation: Book Grants (Public Understan
 ding of Science and Technology)
DESCRIPTION:The one Sloan program that funds individuals directly: grants f
 or authors researching and writing nonfiction books that bring science and
  technology to a general audience. Over 200 authors supported since 1996. 
 Favoured topics include elucidating confusing or controversial scientific 
 subjects\, profiles of figures in science and technology\, science-technol
 ogy-art connections\, women and science\, and the culture and philosophy o
 f science. Start with a letter of inquiry to program director Doron Weber\
 ; full proposals are by invitation only. Reviewed three times a year: LOIs
  by 1 September (decision by 15 February)\, 1 January (by 31 May) and 1 Ma
 y (by 31 October). No application fee.\n\nOrganisation: Alfred P. Sloan Fo
 undation\nLocation: Remote / anywhere (US foundation\; grants paid directl
 y to authors or via a nonprofit host)\nAward: Typically up to $60\,000 per
  book grant\nDuration: Project-based (book research and writing)\n\nMore: 
 https://sloan.org/programs/public-understanding/books?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://sloan.org/programs/public-understanding/books?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote / anywhere (US foundation\; grants paid directly to authors
  or via a nonprofit host)
END:VEVENT
