DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261004
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261005
SUMMARY:Deadline: Printed Matter Publisher Work Grant 2026
DESCRIPTION:Third annual cycle of Printed Matter's Publisher Work Grant\, s
 upported by Wagner Foundation. Three unrestricted grants of $10\,000 go to
  independent artists' book publishers\, acknowledging past work and provid
 ing capacity-building funds for future book projects and publisher sustain
 ability. ELIGIBILITY: independent imprints with an 'independent spirit\,' 
 generally small in scale\, with a publishing history of one or more years 
 and one or more titles per year\, currently active with future titles in t
 he works\; open to publishers based anywhere (international presses encour
 aged). NOT for individual artists seeking to publish their own work\, nor 
 for commercial presses that exclusively publish client work\; more establi
 shed\, well-funded\, or institutionally supported publishers may be deprio
 ritised. Funds are unrestricted (production\, artists' fees\, equipment\, 
 studio costs\, rent\, etc.). Applications reviewed by Printed Matter and a
  guest jury based on the imprint's body of work\, upcoming projects\, and 
 potential impact. Selected presses also receive a highlighted presence at 
 a 2026 Printed Matter Art Book Fair (travel and accommodation are the gran
 tee's responsibility). Deadline: Sunday 4 October 2026\, 11:59PM EST.\n\nO
 rganisation: Printed Matter\nLocation: New York\, USA-based\; open to publ
 ishers based anywhere in the world\nAward: Three unrestricted grants of $1
 0\,000 USD each\, plus a featured exhibitor presence (complimentary table)
  at a forthcoming Printed Matter NY or LA Art Book Fair. No application fe
 e.\nDuration: Unrestricted\, capacity-building award (no obligation to rea
 lise a particular project)\n\nMore: https://www.printedmatter.org/workgran
 t?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.printedmatter.org/workgrant?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New York\, USA-based\; open to publishers based anywhere in the wo
 rld
END:VEVENT
